data.title: AV and OpenJAUS partner to enhance Autonomous Uncrewed System interoperability, benefiting industry and defense sectors.
data.description: A collaboration has been announced between AV and OpenJAUS in Arlington, Virginia. This collaboration aims to enhance interoperability for Autonomous Uncrewed System (UxS). The partnership is expected to benefit both parties, as well as advance the technology in the field. This initiative underscores the growing importance of autonomous systems in various industries. It is a significant step towards achieving seamless integration and cooperation among UxS, ultimately contributing to improved efficiency and effectiveness. Stay tuned for further updates as this collaboration progresses.

data.title: Equifax (NYSE: EFX) CEOs to attend 2 investor conferences in November including J.P. Morgan Ultimate Services Investor Conference.
data.description: Atlanta, on October 31, 2025, Equifax® (NYSE: EFX) announced its participation in two investor conferences scheduled for November. The company's CEO, Mark Begor, and CFO, John Gamble, will take part in the J.P. Morgan Ultimate Services Investor Conference. The purpose of their participation is to provide insights about the company's performance and future prospects to investors. This move indicates Equifax's proactive approach towards investor engagement and transparency.

data.title: 69% of consumers failed to decrease debt in last quarter. Over a quarter (27%) increased their debt.
data.description: In the last three months, the majority of consumer debt has either increased or stayed the same as more families are relying on credit cards to cover expenses. A recent report reveals that 27% of consumers have accumulated additional debt during this period. These findings were highlighted in San Mateo, California, on October 31, 2025.

data.title: Anthropic enhances security with AI Safety Level 3 protocols, specifically against CBRN threats, through Claude Opus 4.
data.description: Anthropic has implemented AI Safety Level 3 guidelines to enhance security and deployment procedures, focusing on protection against CBRN threats. This initiative accompanies the release of Claude Opus 4, aiming to strengthen defense protocols.

data.title: Dominion Energy reports Q3 2025 net income of $1.0 billion ($1.16 per share), up from $934 million ($1.09 per share) in 2024.
data.description: Dominion Energy, Inc. revealed a unaudited net income of $1.0 billion ($1.16 per share) for the three months ending Sept. 30, 2025, in accordance with Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (GAAP). This marks an increase from the net income of $934 million ($1.09 per share) reported for the same period in 2024. The operating earnings (non-GAAP) for the three months ending Sept. 30, 2025, stood at $921 million ($1.06 per share).

data.title: Clearmind Medicine files U.S. patent for neuroplastogen MEAI therapy to treat cocaine addiction.
data.description: In Vancouver, Canada, on October 31, 2025, Clearmind Medicine Inc. made an announcement regarding the publication of a U.S. patent application. Clearmind is a clinical-stage biotech company listed on Nasdaq as CMND and on FSE as CWY0. The company is dedicated to developing innovative neuroplastogen-derived therapeutics for addressing significant, yet undertreated, health issues. The patent application extends the coverage of their non-hallucinogenic compound, 5-methoxy-2-aminoindane (MEAI), specifically for combating cocaine addiction. This development signifies a significant step in Clearmind's efforts to tackle addiction problems.
